<paragraph blockId="56.[264,1322,1134,1241]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
The Latin 
<emphasis box="[438,536,1175,1200]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">&quot;serrus&quot;</emphasis>
means sawteeth, referring to the cerci, which have a pair of sawteeth posteriorly.
